Security Recommendations
1. Enable Multi-Factor Authentication

Adds an extra layer of security by requiring two forms of verification.

2. Strong Password Policy

Reduces the risk of unauthorized access.

3. Regular Software Updates

Fixes known security vulnerabilities.

4. Employee Security Training

Helps users recognize cyber threats.

5. Regular Data Backups

Allows quick recovery after attacks.

6. Install Antivirus Software

Detects and removes malware.

7. Configure Firewalls

Blocks unauthorized network access.

8. Encrypt Sensitive Data

Protects confidential information.

9. Limit User Access

Provides only the permissions users need.

10. Monitor Systems Regularly

Detects suspicious activities early.